Against all odds, lowly-rated and less fancied South Africa dumped Mohamed Salah’s Egypt out of the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON)  and setting up an interesting quarter-finals fixture with Nigeria’s Super Eagles on Wednesday. South Africa hit Egypt on the counter-attack as Thembinkosi Lorch calmly slotted into the corner. The hosts’ best chance fell to Mahmoud Trezeguet, but he could only fire his shot straight at Ronwen Williams.  Details layer….  Anthony Nlebem